HTML Text Formatting Tags

Common Formatting Tags:
--Tag	Meaning	Display
<b>	: Bold (non-important)
<strong>	: Strong importance	
<i> :	Italic (non-important)
<em>	: Emphasis (semantic italic)	
<u>	: Underline
<mark>	: Highlighted/Marked text

Example Code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>HTML Text Formatting</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Day 5: Text Formatting in HTML</h1>

    <p>This is <b>bold</b> using the <code>&lt;b&gt;</code> tag.</p>
    <p>This is <strong>strongly important</strong> using <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code>.</p>
    
    <p>This is <i>italic</i> using <code>&lt;i&gt;</code>.</p>
    <p>This is <em>emphasized</em> using <code>&lt;em&gt;</code>.</p>
    
    <p>This is <u>underlined</u> using <code>&lt;u&gt;</code>.</p>
    <p>This is <mark>highlighted</mark> using <code>&lt;mark&gt;</code>.</p>
  </body>
</html>

Notes:
--<strong> and <em> are semantic â€” they help with SEO and accessibility.
--Use <b> and <i> when it's purely visual, not meaning-based.
